 The Nigerian Army has again failed to appear before the Lagos state judicial panel on ”#EndSARS”.
The panel was set up to investigate allegations of police brutality and the incident of October 20, 2020 where soldiers opened fire on protesters at the Lekki tollgate.
The army was expected to appear on Saturday to respond to some petitions brought before the panel.
